en_104633_0	US Secretary of State John Kerry told the ongoing session of the Human Rights Council in Geneva that an opportunity has dawned for Sri Lanka to achieve a real change.
en_104633_1	He said that the UN Human Rights Council has taken steps to encourage Sri Lankan leaders to fulfill their promises and pledges made to the people.
en_104633_2	The US Secretary of State reiterated that the UN Human Rights Council procedure cannot be ignored in that process.
en_104633_3	He expressed these views commonly for Sri Lankan and Myanmar during his speech at the inauguration of the 28th session of the Human Rights Council today.
